OL,4,G0100FFace the Music
OL,5,     GJoseph Cooper invites viewers to
OL,6,     Gmatch their musical wits against
OL,7,     Gguests Joyce Grenfell, Bernard
OL,8,     GLevin and Robin Ray. With guest
OL,9,     Gmusician Dame Eva Turner.
OL,10,G0130FCaroline Walker: Women's Work
OL,11,     GAcclaimed Scottish artist
OL,12,     GCaroline Walker paints the
OL,13,     Ginvisible labour that shapes
OL,14,     Gwomen's lives, from housework to
OL,15,     Gcaregiving to creative production.
OL,16,G0230FTreasures of Ancient Egypt
OL,17,     GAlastair Sooke concludes the
OL,18,     Gstory of Egyptian art by looking
OL,19,     Gat how, despite political
OL,20,     Gdecline, the final era of Egypt's
OL,21,     Gempire saw its art enjoy revival
OL,22,     Gand rebirth.
